February 5, 2017 5:07 pm Updated: February 5, 2017 5:16 pm ‘Serious’ two-vehicle crash blocks Highway 39 near Moose Jaw, Sask. By Thomas Piller Online Producer Global News 
Moose Jaw RCMP are advising Saskatchewan motorists that Highway 39 is blocked due to a two-vehicle crash. File / Global News What is this?

Moose Jaw, Sask., RCMP are advising drivers that Highway 39 is blocked due to a “serious” two-vehicle crash. 
The collision occurred on Highway 39, approximately five kilometres south of Highway 1. 
READ MORE: Sask. police ticket man who hasn’t held valid driver’s licence in past 15 years 
Highway 39 traffic is expected to be restricted until Sunday evening as RCMP conduct their investigation. 
Police officials are asking motorists to use caution while travelling in this area due to winter road conditions. Drivers can utilize alternate routes via highways 1, 624 or 339. Related
